Context()->variables->are(C=>'Real',F=>'Real');
parser::Assignment->Allow;
$solve=Formula("F=-7.6");

subsection.p:
Using function notation we write
                \frac{\Delta f}{\Delta s}\amp=\frac{f(25)-f(5)}{25-5}
                \amp=\frac{27-10}{25-5}
                \amp=0.85
            The number 0.85 (notice it is positive) means that between speeds of 5 and 25, the car's efficiency is increasing at an average rate of 0.85 per 1.

setup.pg-code:
Context("ImplicitPlane")->flags->set(reduceConstants=>0);
$x1 = Real(1);
$x2 = Real(random(3, 5, 1));
$b = Real(random(1,3,1));
$a = Real(lcm($x1**2+$b,$x2**2+$b))*random(1,3,1);
$f = Formula("$a/(x^2+$b)");
$y1 = $f->eval(x=>$x1);
$y2 = $f->eval(x=>$x2);
$Dy = $y2 - $y1;
$Dx = $x2 - $x1;
$slope = Formula("$Dy/$Dx");
$line = Compute("y = $slope*(x - $x1) + $y1");
